{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"292b7f81-2332-4ccf-af66-2720ab4e727d","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 release notes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/whats-new/) and update NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a8a1aee-10e0-4ff3-90b0-57ad28df176f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"400F:56360:1668C3C:193B277:69F94AD9"},"id":"e9570253-7f23-4068-8af4-502ef3356c1e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:41:51.587Z","parentId":"b7213c4b-7692-4d60-953a-7fd4c36d934a"}
